items.sentence: I don't think you need to tell Tom everything.
I don't think that we should do that with Tom.
I don't think that Tom is supposed to be here.
Tom told Mary that she'd done the right thing.
Tom lost his footing and fell down the stairs.
Tom stole some money from his father's wallet.
Tom told me he didn't remember what Mary said.
I knew that Tom would do that sooner or later.
I knew that Tom would likely agree to do that.
I knew that Tom would show you how to do that.
